cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques to interpret health-related data collected through the Internet of Things (IoT) for personalized healthcare. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the use of AI techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses the conversion of big data to smart data, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the use of semantic perception approach, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of kHealth technology for Asthma and other diseases, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
